@startuml dynamic_data_normalization
!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/behavioral/activity-diagram-style.iuml

title Dynamic Data Normalization Architecture\nDe-duplication examines blocks before storage and replaces redundant blocks with pointers

start
:Cloud consumer writes data block;
:De-duplication system receives block
(prior to storage controllers);
:Compute hash of incoming block;
:Look up hash in
hash-and-piece index;
if (Hash already in index?) then (yes\n(redundant block))
  :Eliminate duplicate block;
  :Create pointer to original block;
  :Save pointer;
else (no\n(new block))
  :Save new block to storage;
  :Update hash-and-piece index;
endif
:Pass result to storage controllers;
stop

note right
  Applies to block- and file-based
  storage (most effective on block).
  Usable for disk storage and
  backup tape drives.
end note

note left
  Without de-duplication, redundant
  copies cause:
  - inflated billed storage
  - wasted online + backup space
  - slower cataloging and backup
  - longer replication times
end note

@enduml
